7.4.asStringPrec(5)
7.4.asStringPrec(50)
::

subsection::Using Floats as replacement for Integers

Because in SuperCollider, an link::Classes/Integer:: is only 16 bit, it may be useful to calculate with floats also when only whole numbers are needed. You can use 64 bit floats for integer calculations up to code::9007199254740992:: (code::2 ^ 53::, or about code::9 x 10^15::)

code::
a = 2 ** 53 - 1
b = a + 1;
c = a + 2;
b - a // correct (1)
c - a // incorrect (also 1)
::

